snippet.textDisplay:
*When he said kobe was like Magic he made you feel like he knew u for 25 years made me remember when I 1st moved to L.A. trying to pursue being a young lil actress.
I met a girl who invited me to a party that was at Prince's club Glam Slam. She said, Magic's gonna call you. (It was Magic's party)
I.m thinking, YEA riiight!
The next day, my cousin comes to my room and says, "MAGIC JOHNSON'S on the phone for you???"
I looked at her like 😳

I answered and he said, "Hi, (my name), This is Magic"
I could NOT believe it. And he officially invited me to the party! 😊 He was soooooooo nice.
I was just a girl from KY!
I have never forgotten that call.

I didn't know kobe, but I can only imagine how he made everyone he ever met, feel Just like that...and how kind and thoughtful and how such a beautiful person he was to others the way Magic Johnson was to me. A stranger.
God bless the souls of everyone who passed. God was ready for them Now. Hopefully we can lift each other up and celebrate their lives and the fact that they are now with God.
It helps knowing that!💝

snippet.textDisplay:
April 13, 2020 (4132020) is the next Mamba Day (If we add up all the numbers, you get: 4+1+3+2+0+2+0 = 12; 1 + 2 = 3).
That day is exactly 78 days from January 26, 2020, the day Kobe, and Gianna, and all the others died.

78 + 3 = 81.

Just still trying make sense out of everything. Still feels like a bad dream to me. We miss you Kobe.

#Mamba24Life

snippet.textDisplay: I'm still trying to process this but move on at the same time.  I've realized that the time that we have is precious and everyone should know that because when you lose a family member, a friend, a competitor, a teammate, etc., your heart just shatters you.  There is no answers to life outside of this world but God has the answers that we seek, and I promise you that he will hear your call and listen to what your feeling.  If I had one word that I could say to Kobe's family and all the other families that were in this horrific and tragic accident, it would be just pray every day because he is listening and talking to you each and every day.  As people have said time is short and you got to spend time with your love ones that care about you.  Kobe Bryant we miss you so much and your daughter Gigi.  As a Mavericks fan and watched you played, may God guide you in peace and harmony with your daughter Gigi.  RIP Kobe Bryant!!!!! 😔😞😔😞😔

snippet.textDisplay: I'm not a sports fan n im in NY and I was one of the 1st to find out on accident sunday am...I said no way, I didn't know that! So I kept googling and there was nothing nothing nothing and then suddenly it started showing up, I'm 44 today actually (jan 30) & I remember him in the beginning and all the things he went thru as a young party sports NBA player still underage probably lol but man, he really grew up and my God, the way Gigi looked at him was absolutely beautiful! I think if they had gone any other way than with each other, they would have died emotionally anyway and at least they had each other to comfort in their last moments. I don't think its it's gits great they died, I'm saying I think its beautiful that these two peas in a pod, father-daughter bonded pair went thw way God intended, comforting each other to the end. RIH to all involved in this horrific tragic accident.
